    <div class="crowd-tip"><strong>Best months:</strong> Late September and late March align with the equinoxes, which historically produce the highest aurora activity. January and February offer the longest dark windows each night. September has the advantage of warmer temperatures — outdoor waiting is more comfortable than in midwinter. March combines high solar activity probability with temperatures that are still manageable. Always check both the KP forecast (spaceweather.no) and the cloud forecast (yr.no) before going out.</div>
